	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-08-14T07:02:21">TLA Worldwide PLC is an integrated talent representation and sports marketing company. The Company operates through two segments: Baseball Representation and Sports Marketing. Its Baseball Representation segment primarily assists the on field activities of baseball players, including all aspects of a player's contract negotiation. Its Sports Marketing segment primarily assists the off-field activities of athletes; it represents broadcasters and coaches in respect of their contract negotiations; manages and produces events, primarily in sports and media consultancy. The Company is also an agency in baseball and Australian Football League players (AFL). Its golf business is a service agency with a diverse client base. The Company's broadcasting business is responsible for the representation of media personalities, producers and directors for all facets of their career in television, radio, print and Internet.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-09-16T01:10:21">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, TLA Worldwide Plc revenues increased from $10M to $21.2M. Net loss totaled $1.9M vs. income of $1M. Revenues reflect Sports Marketing segment increase from $3.6M to $14M, Baseball representation segment increase of 13% to $7.2M. Net loss reflects Unallocated segment loss increase from $1.4M to $5M. Basic Earnings per Share excluding Extraordinary Items decreased from $0.01 to -$0.02.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
